column1: I met you when I had a dream Not so long ago
It seems that we closed down a million bars Yeah, you and me, we've come so far
You showed me how to write a song We wrote some right, we wrote some wrong
I was down and out, you let me in And I, you were my only friend
So long Nashville, Tennessee You can't have what's left of me
And as far as I can tell It's high time I wish you well
You built me up, you set me free And you tore down my memories
So you be you and I'll be me So long Nashville, Tennessee
Now you won't miss me when I'm gone You're custom made for moving on
And time to time I'll pass you by A face that I don't recognize
And who knows, maybe years from now You'll be the one I think about
